    <item>
      <title>Echoes of Diva</title>
      <author>V--R</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/672779</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/672779#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">2145ffc70ea56d829b1e236ea53150e2f90635b1</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 09:15:59 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/69ef1a4f6946f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/69ef1a4f674df.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/69ef1a4f77a67.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/69ef1a4f5fdf7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/69ef1a4f7ca6b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/69ef1a4f7d5c8.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Fixes + stamp suit.&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;I dislike the stamp suit and want to replace the Stamp Man entirely. But for now he survives, and so does his suit which Miku must wear.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Adjustment&lt;/em&gt;: Fixed Zatsune attire.&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Adjustment&lt;/em&gt;: Fixed colors of player map icons.&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: Added stamp suit.&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is an extensive mod that replaces Zelda with Hatsune Miku! The mod is still in development but I have some big plans. I'd also love to get some help on some parts that I haven't been able to figure out how to handle yet.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod replaces Zelda with Miku with all outfits compatible. The Tri Rod has been replaced with a leek. The Hylian castle flowers have also been replaced with leeks in Miku's honor.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Dialogue has been adjusted to match these changes with references of royalty removed, connections of Miku as the King's daughter removed. Princess in most cases has been replaced with Vocaloid or idol. Priestess with songstress. Tri Rod with leek. If you spot any lines that I forgot to replace or that don't flow nicely please let me know.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Models a mix of original and modified content from Project Mirai 2.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If anyone wants to throw suggestions about npcs to replace with Vocaloids/Utaus feel free to throw them in the comments. Keep in mind generally what the npc says, their voice, and animations. Replaced characters will use the same general size, animations, and voices but actual dialogue can be adjusted.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Future Plans&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;hr&gt;The following are some ideas I'd like to incorporate into the mod down the line but I'll need some help before they can be achieved.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul class="SelectedElement"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Zelda Sound Replacement - I need help finding where her sound effects are stored and someone with access to a Miku voicebank to produce the sounds.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Tri Replacement - I've made a little Miku in a floating box as a reference to the original Project DIVA opening and it works well but currently there's a leftover glow effect from Tri that I need help editing Common.ptcl to remove.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Link Teto Replacement - I need help with adjusting Link to show properly in his own cutscenes and removing his glow/fire effects in Common.ptcl.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;NPC Replacements - I'd like to replace random npc characters with Vocaloids and Utaus.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Known Issues&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cutting the leeks in the castle still have the original particles. I'm assuming this is also controlled by Common.ptcl.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Currently the dialogue for acquiring Miku's bed calls it Zelda's bed and I can't spot where in the files that is. The echo itself is properly labeled.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Link looks wrong during the intro and Ganon boss fight.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;"ZeldaClothes02" aka the royal travel attire aka in this mod customary attire needs some rigging adjustments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Donate&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;hr&gt;If you like this mod and want to support the development of it and other mods consider joining my &lt;a href="https://www.patreon.com/c/VRArt1" target="_blank"&gt;Patreon&lt;/a&gt; or sending me a tip through &lt;a href="https://ko-fi.com/vrart1" target="_blank"&gt;Ko-Fi&lt;/a&gt;!</description>
